2) explanation : 
Intuition
The goal is to display the exact string provided as input.
Simply take the input string and pass it to the print function.
No processing or modification is needed—just output it as it is.

Approach
Read the input string into a variable named input_string and print it as it is.

Pseudocode :
/* Function to print the input string */
printString(input_string) {
    /* Print the input string */
    print input_string;
}

Actual Code : in python

def printString(input_string):
    print(input_string)    // It simply prints the string as-is & length doesn’t matter (Python strings can be huge)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    input_string = input()          
    printString(input_string)

👌
Rule for DSA / CP
If problem is about value → use int
If problem is about length / format → use string
